<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Custody" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Custody,</orth> a keeping, guarding: <cit><quote>gaoler, take him to thy c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. I, 1, 156</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>how darest thou trust so great a charge from thine own c.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 1.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 61</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>whilst 'tis in my c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.164" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 164</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>